Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
proto_design(25.10)                                        proto_design(25.10)

Name
       proto_design

Syntax
       proto_design

       [-help]

       [-constraints <name>]

       [-summary <file>_<name>]

       Generates  an  initial  floorplan for prototyping that can be used as a
       start point for making the final floorplan. It is a super command  that
       places flexModels, power domains, and/or user-specified module seeds.

       Note:  The  proto_design command supports multiple levels of hierarchy,
       such as nested partitions and nested power  domains.  To  support  this
       feature, you can use the set_proto_mode -proto_design_level multi_level
       option.  You also have a choice to run proto_design to place FlexModels
       and/or macro blocks for each level of hierarchy  for  better  placement
       QOR.

       By  default, the proto_design command makes settings internally so that
       FlexModel floorplans are available even though  any  user-defined  set-
       tings  are  not  made.  However,  if  you  make  any  changes, then the
       proto_design command settings will be overwritten. This  feature  helps
       to improve the usability.

       Note: The proto_design command honors the fence spacing rules.

Parameters
       -constraints <name>
              Specifies  the  constraint  file  name  (string).  Uses the con-
              straints specified in the constraint file for fence creation and
              module guide generation. A constraint file is a text  file  that
              can contain a list of seeds used when generating fences and mod-
              ule  guides,  and  basic  relative, spacing and orientation con-
              straints to follow during macro placement.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  proto_design parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

               man proto_design

       -summary <file>_<name>
              Specifies  the  name of the file in which the summary output re-
              port with some checkPoints like violation summary,  TU  of  mod-
              ules, master/clones shape are written.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
       The  following  example  invokes  proto_design  with the specified con-
       straint file proto_user_constraint.txt file with all the  default  set-
       tings:

       set_proto_design_mode -timing_aware true

       proto_design -constraints proto_user_constraint.txt

